race.comment: CHERYL'S SHOUT (1) is racing well without winning, finishing 1.8L off the winner at Albany last time out as the race favourite. This looks much easier than that event and the 2kg claim of Webster comes in handy. Can roll forward from the draw and can return to winning ways. GINGERIFFIC (8) won well at Geraldton two back before disappointing at Northam last time out. The rise in trip looks a big key to her chances today however and the stable's strike jockey has been engaged. Can bounce back to winning ways. ENCHANTING SOUND (3) is better than she showed first-up and can improve. DRAG MACHINE (2) looks well placed back to this event.
